The article is a transcript of a press gaggle with White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs aboard Air Force One en route to Mexico City. The main topics discussed include the ongoing policy in Afghanistan and Pakistan, the purpose of President Obama's visit to Mexico, the economy, energy and climate change, safety and security, gun trafficking, the trucking issue, the Merida Initiative, and the Summit of the Americas. Gibbs also addresses questions about the President's previous visits to Latin America, Cuba, workers' rights in Mexico, and the renewal of the assault weapons ban.